      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The main risk with extremely high Vitamin D doses is hypercalcemia, which is an excess of calcium in the blood, potentially leading to kidney issues. If you feel perfectly fine, the immediate risk is low, but your body doesn't always give warnings before imbalances occur. Since this is a potent dose, I strongly recommend having your blood correlated before and after the intake to ensure you are safe.",
